title: Mr Hogarth's Will
creator: Catherine Helen Spence
description: LibriVox recording of Mr Hogarth's Will by Catherine Helen Spence. For more information about the readers, visit http://librivox.org/mr-hogarths-will-by-catherine-helen-spence/. Jane and Elsie Melville were raised by their kindly but eccentric uncle, Mr Hogarth who believed that women were just as good as men, and thus gave his nieces a boy's education. Upon his death, they find that he has left his entire fortune to his heretofore unknown son and left them only a small allowance, expecting them to make their own way in the world using the education he furnished them. Will the girls survive in a world that expects them, at the most, to become governesses? (summary by Karen Savage) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B Part 1 (188MB) Download M4B Part 2 (193MB)
